text: The John W. Bennett House is a historic two-story house in Brownville, Nebraska. It was built in 1868 as an I-house for John W. Bennett, a farmer from Kentucky. With It is "the oldest, dated example of the I-house in Nebraska." It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since September 16, 1983. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Nemaha County, Nebraska Category:Houses completed in 1868 Category:I-houses Category:1868 establishments in Nebraska
